            for Health and Welfare on 18 July 1988 and deposited in the Land Registry;
            <sourceNote>(<ref href="/hk/1993/8">8 of 1993 s.
                30</ref>; <ref href="hk/2019/er5">E.R. 5 of
                2019</ref>; <ref href="hk/2024/21">21 of 2024 s. 78</ref>)</sourceNote></def><def class="first_line_indent_-24 left_indent_24 " name="MarineWaters"><term>marine
                waters</term>
                (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">海洋水域</term>) means waters within the Southern Water
            Control Zone boundary below the high water mark;</def><def class="first_line_indent_-24 left_indent_24 " name="MuiWoASubzone"><term>Mui
                Wo (A)
            Subzone</term>
                (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">梅窩(A)分區</term>) means all that area bounded by the
            river catchment boundary in the west, and by a line between a point north of Tseng Tau
            San Tsuen
                (22º16<i>&apos;</i>26<i>&quot;</i>N,
                113º59<i>&apos;</i>02<i>&quot;</i>E)
            and a point east of Lung Mei Hang
                (22º16<i>&apos;</i>16<i>&quot;</i>N,
                113º59<i>&apos;</i>05<i>&quot;</i>E)
            in the east, which is delineated and marked MW(A) on the Map, and which includes the
            areas of Lin Fa Shan, Lung Mei Tsuen and Lung Mei Hang;</def><def class="first_line_indent_-24 left_indent_24 " name="MuiWoBSubzone"><term>Mui
                Wo (B)
            Subzone</term>
